# Product Description Generator Rules

## Code Organization
- All route definitions should be in app/routes.py
- Business logic belongs in app/services/
- Static assets (CSS, JS) go in app/static/
- HTML templates stored in app/templates/
- Uploaded images stored in app/static/uploads/

## Naming Conventions
- Use snake_case for Python variables, functions, and files
- Use PascalCase for class names
- CSS classes should use kebab-case
- JavaScript variables and functions use camelCase

## Code Formatting
- Use 4 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- Maximum line length of 88 characters
- Follow PEP 8 guidelines for Python code
- Add docstrings to all functions and classes

## API Integration
- Store all API keys in the .env file (never commit to version control)
- Use environment variables for configuration settings
- Handle API errors gracefully with proper user feedback

## Security
- Sanitize all user inputs
- Validate all file uploads (type, size, content)
- Implement proper error handling
- Use secure routes for sensitive operations

## Performance
- Optimize large image processing
- Use caching where appropriate
- Minimize JavaScript and CSS file sizes

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all service functions
- Test API integrations with proper mocking
- Validate UI components across devices 